'''to flimflam''' (v.) (derogatory)


To make comments that are lacking in content or clear meaning, to say things which are unfalsifiable or empty.


Also:

'''a flimflammer''' (n.) one who flimflams

'''flimmflammery''' (n.) talk which could be described as flimflam

'''flimflamming''' (adj.)

'''flimflammingly''' (adv.)

E.g.

"''He never says anything staright, he just flimflams"

"I'm sick of his flimflammery"

"She's a flimflamming idiot"''